---
@META
dir: prisma
updated: 2026-03-18
files: 4
stack: Prisma 7, PostgreSQL, TypeScript

@EXPORTS
schema.prisma: PrismaSchema — 18 models: User, Account, Session, VerificationToken, Chapter, CompletedChapter, ChapterProgress, Achievement, UserAchievement, CognitiveGlitchAttempt, ChapterCompletion, QuestionAnswer, ProjectSubmission, ModuleTestAttempt, Question, Hackathon, Team, TeamMember, HackathonProject, GraduateProfile
seed.ts: seed — seed script for chapters, achievements, and initial data
seed-questions.ts: seedQuestions — seed questions into DB from static data

@INTERFACES
User: { id, email, emailVerified, name, image, password, username, xp, level, currentStreak, longestStreak, isAdmin, createdAt, updatedAt + relations }
Chapter: { id, chapterId:unique, title, description, xpReward, difficulty, order + questions[], completedBy[], progress[] }
ChapterCompletion: { userId, chapterId, completedChapter:bool, answeredQuestions:bool, submittedProject:bool } — 3-star system
QuestionAnswer: { userId, chapterId, questionId, answer, correct, xpEarned } — @@unique([userId,chapterId,questionId])
ModuleTestAttempt: { userId, moduleNumber, score, totalQuestions, timeElapsed, attemptNumber, completed, xpEarned, moduleStars }
Question: { chapterId, questionNumber, questionText, options:Json, correctAnswer:int, explanation?, xpReward }
Hackathon: { title, description, theme, startDate, endDate, status, maxTeamSize, prizes:Json, judges:Json, sponsors:Json }
Team: { name, hackathonId + members[], project? }
HackathonProject: { teamId:unique, hackathonId, title, description, githubUrl, technologies:Json, score?, placement?, feedback:Json? }
GraduateProfile: { userId:unique, bio?, certificateId:unique, skills:Json, portfolio:Json, linkedIn?, github?, lookingForWork }

@PROCESSES
Migrate: `npx prisma migrate dev` → create/apply migrations
Generate: `npx prisma generate` → regenerate client
Seed: `npm run db:seed` → tsx prisma/seed.ts
Studio: `npx prisma studio` → web GUI on :5555

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: none
external: @prisma/client, tsx

@STANDARDS
- PostgreSQL only (no SQLite)
- UUID primary keys everywhere
- Composite unique constraints for user+entity pairs
- Performance indexes on all frequently queried fields
- Json fields for flexible data (prizes, judges, options, skills, portfolio)
- Prisma 7 with pg adapter — configured in prisma.config.ts at root

@WARNINGS
- 4 migration files — schema evolved from init → rename leson→chapter → add questions → add arena
- Prisma 7 adapter requires pg Pool — see src/lib/prisma.ts
- seed.ts depends on static data from src/data/chapters.ts
---
